    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Chop your<strong> cherry tomatoes</strong> in half, then peel and finely slice (don't chop) your<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Add your<strong> fennel seeds</strong> to a<strong> pestle & mortar</strong> and grind (or chop if you don't have a pestle and mortar!) to a fine powder</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-nduja-and-fennel-seed-spaghetti/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> halved cherry tomatoes</strong> with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until beginning to soften</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-nduja-and-fennel-seed-spaghetti/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>spaghetti</strong> to a pot of plenty of<strong> boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the<strong> spaghetti</strong> for 8-10 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the<strong> spaghetti</strong> and return to the pot, reserving a cup of the<strong> starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-nduja-and-fennel-seed-spaghetti/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the tomatoes are beginning to soften, add the <strong>sliced garlic</strong> and<strong> crushed fennel seeds</strong> and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Add your<strong> Chinese rice wine</strong> and cook for a further 30 secs</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-nduja-and-fennel-seed-spaghetti/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong>, then add to the pan along with your <strong>'Nduja </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)<strong> </strong>and 50ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[65ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[80ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> and give everything a good mix up until fully combined and the spinach has wilted</p><p>Season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and cook for a further 3-4 min or until a sauce has formed</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-nduja-and-fennel-seed-spaghetti/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel <strong>half</strong> your <strong>Italian hard cheese</strong> until you end up with a pile of cheese shavings</p><p>Grate the<strong> remaining Italian hard cheese</strong></p><p>Chop your<strong> basil</strong> finely, including the stalks, keeping the stalks and leaves separate</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-nduja-and-fennel-seed-spaghetti/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>basil stalks</strong> to the sauce with your <strong>soft cheese</strong> and stir it all together</p><p>Add the<strong> drained spaghetti</strong> with the <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong> and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>creamy</strong> <strong>'Nduja & fennel seed spaghetti</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of the starchy pasta water if your sauce is looking a little dry</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-nduja-and-fennel-seed-spaghetti/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> creamy 'Nduja & fennel seed spaghetti</strong> topped with the <strong>cheese shavings</strong> and <strong>chopped basil leaves</strong></p><p>Season with a grind of<strong> black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
